The article is a speech given by President Biden at the McCain Institute in Phoenix, Arizona. He emphasizes the importance of defending American democracy and speaks about the dangers of election denialism and political violence. He mentions the threat to institutions, the Constitution, and the character of the nation. President Biden acknowledges that democracy is not a partisan issue but an American issue. He also criticizes the extremist MAGA movement within the Republican Party, stating that their agenda would fundamentally alter American democracy. He calls on all Americans, regardless of political affiliation, to stand up for democracy and the values embodied in the Declaration of Independence. President Biden emphasizes that the decisions made today will shape the future of the country and the world. He urges Americans to fulfill their responsibility in preserving democracy for the sake of future generations.